<p dir="auto"><a href="https://github.com/csstools/postcss-plugins/tree/main/plugins/postcss-image-set-function">PostCSS image-set() Function</a> lets you display resolution-dependent images
using the <code>image-set()</code> function in CSS, following the <a href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-images-4/#image-set-notation" rel="nofollow">CSS Images</a>
specification.</p>
<p dir="auto"><a href="https://caniuse.com/#feat=css-image-set" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/9c4e0533d28411729391093e0063fefeda2b69f93c42dabc498015cbb5ef7622/68747470733a2f2f63616e697573652e626974736f66636f2e64652f696d6167652f6373732d696d6167652d7365742e706e67" alt="'Can I use' table" data-canonical-src="https://caniuse.bitsofco.de/image/css-image-set.png" style="max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
